[0.000, "o", "[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mfunnel is a conversation, not a form. One thread per spec, one channel per project. The bot drives the \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mfunnel like the CLI skills do -- it probes, proposes, and the user confirms or pushes back. LLM inference \u001b[39m   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mstays server-side -- the sidecar proxies the conversation to the server, which runs the same authoring logic\u001b[39m \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m the CLI skills use. The sidecar is still a thin client, it just has a new transport.\u001b[39m                        \u001b[49m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;78;186;101mвҸә\u001b[1C\u001b[39m\u001b[1mSkill\u001b[22m(specgraph-shape)\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m \u001b[1CвҺҝ\u001b[1CВ \u001b[39mSuccessfully\u001b[1Cloaded\u001b[1Cskill\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mвҸә\u001b[1C\u001b[39mLet\u001b[1Cme\u001b[1Cload\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cprerequisites\u001b[1Cand\u001b[1Ckick\u001b[1Coff\u001b[1Cbackground\u001b[1Cresearch\u001b[1Cin\u001b[1Cparallel.\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;78;186;101mвҸә\u001b[1C\u001b[39m\u001b[1mBash\u001b[22m(go\u001b[1Crun\u001b[1C./cmd/specgraph\u001b[1Chealth\u001b[1C2>&1)\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;1"]
