[0.245, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2D\u001b[4B\r\u001b[2C\u001b[6A\u001b[1mDecisions 6-8 are architecturally coupled\u001b[1C\u001b[22mвҖ”\u001b[1Cthey\u001b[1Cform\u001b[1Ca\u001b[1Csingle\u001b[1Cdesign\u001b[1Cchoice:\u001b[1C\"the\u001b[1Cserver\u001b[1Cis\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cauthoring\r\u001b[1B  brain, clients are transport adapters.\" This is a bigger commitment than the original spec's \"sidecar calls\r\u001b[1B   existing\u001b[1CRPCs.\"\u001b[1CIt\u001b[1Cmeans\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cserver\u001b[1Cgains\u001b[1CLLM\u001b[1Corchestration,\u001b[1Csession\u001b[1Cstate,\u001b[1Cand\u001b[1Cprompt\u001b[1Cmanagement.\u001b[1CThe\r\u001b[1B  payoff is that every future transport (web UI, VS Code extension, another chat platform) gets authoring for\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B free.                                                                                                  \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                      \r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ"]
