[0.173, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2D\u001b[4B\r\u001b[2C\u001b[6A\u001b[1mWhat just happened architecturally\u001b[22m:\u001b[1CThe\u001b[1Coriginal\u001b[1Cslack-authoring\u001b[1Cwas\u001b[1Ca\u001b[1C\u001b[3mread + approve\u001b[1C\u001b[23mintegration\u001b[1CвҖ”\u001b[1Cthe\r\u001b[1B  sidecar called existing RPCs and rendered results. The amended version is a \u001b[3mfull authoring transport\u001b[23m вҖ” it  \r\u001b[1B  requires\u001b[1Ca\u001b[1C\u001b[1mnew server-side capability\u001b[1C\u001b[22m(conversation\u001b[1Cengine\u001b[1Cwith\u001b[1CLLM\u001b[1Corchestration)\u001b[1Cthat\u001b[1Cdoesn't\u001b[1Cexist\u001b[1Cyet.\r\u001b[1B  This is the difference between \"add a client\" and \"add a platform capability that enables new clients.\" The\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B conversation engine is the real deliverable; Slack is just the first consumer.                          \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[39m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ"]
